# Root-level Application Code

All main application source code is now copied to root-level folders:

- **api/** — Express REST API server (port 3001)
  - server.js — Main entry point
  - lib/ — JWT, crypto, Prisma, Twilio utilities
  - middleware/ — CSRF, rate limiting, auth
  - routes/ — API endpoints
  - services/ — Background jobs, Socket.IO integration
  - utils/ — Logger, security helpers

- **socket/** — Socket.IO WebSocket server (port 3002)
  - socket-server.js — Main entry point
  - lib/ — Socket utilities and helpers

- **web/** — Next.js 14 frontend (port 3000)
  - app/ — Next.js App Router
  - components/ — React UI components
  - lib/ — Frontend utilities
  - styles/ — Global CSS and Tailwind

- **shared/** — Shared types, utilities, and schemas
  - index.ts — Barrel exports
  - types/ — TypeScript type definitions
  - utils/ — Shared utility functions
  - schemas/ — JSON schemas for validation

## Entry Points

```bash
# API server (root-level)
node api/server.js

# Socket.IO server (root-level)
node socket/socket-server.js

# Next.js frontend (root-level)
npm run dev:web
```

This flattened structure makes it easier to review and maintain all application code directly from the project root.
